\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi250\li19\ri62\sl-202\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw1\fs21 Pretty soon I was feeling my familiar way through the \expndtw3 thirty or so blankets and rugs Pa has got hung around to \expndtw-3 slow down the escape of air from the Nest, and I wasn't quite \expndtw-2 so scared. I began to hear the tick-ticking of the clocks in the \expndtw1 Nest and knew I was getting back into air, because there's \expndtw-3 no sound outside in the vacuum, of course. But my mind was \expndtw2 still crawly and uneasy as I pushed through the last blan\-\expndtw-2 kets-Pa's got them faced with aluminum foil to hold in the \expndtw0 heat-and came into the Nest.\cf0\lang2057\fs20\par
\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi250\li10\ri67\sl-202\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw2\fs21 Let me tell you about the Nest. It's low and snug, just \expndtw-2 room for the four of us and our things. The floor is covered \expndtw-1 with thick woolly rugs. Three of the sides are blankets, and \expndtw-2 the blankets roofing it touch Pa's head. He tells me it's inside \expndtw-1 a much bigger room, but I've never seen the real walls or \expndtw-4 ceiling.\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\fs20\par
