\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi245\li53\ri5\sl-197\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw2\fs21 It's Pa who is the chief guardian of the fire, though. I \expndtw-3 always think of him that way: a tall man sitting cross-legged, \expndtw0 frowning anxiously at the fire, his lined face golden in its \expndtw-4 light, and every so often carefully placing on it a piece of coal \expndtw-1 from the big heap beside it. Pa tells me there used to be \expndtw-2 guardians of the fire sometimes in the very old days-vestal \expndtw0 virgins, he calls them-although there was unfrozen air all \expndtw1 around then and you didn't really need one,\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\fs20\par
