\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi245\li24\ri19\sl-197\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\fs21 Pa says air is tiny molecules that fly away like a flash if \expndtw1 there isn't something to stop them. We have to watch \expndtw2 not to let the air run low. Pa always keeps a big reserve \expndtw0 supply of it \scaps ib \scaps0 buckets behind the first blankets, along with \expndtw-1 extra coal and cans of food and other things, such as pails of \expndtw-6 snow to melt for water. We have to go way down to the bottom \expndtw1 floor for that stuff, which is a mean trip, and get it through \expndtw-2 a door to outside.\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\fs20\par
