\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi245\ri48\sl-197\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw-2 He had lost about 20 pounds. As he only weighed 140 to \expndtw0 start with, this left little to go on with. His knees and wrist bones stuck out like rocks under the skin. His feet were all \expndtw-3 swollen and chewed-looking from the Camp boots; he hadn't \expndtw0 dared take the boots off, the last three days of walking, be\-\expndtw-2 cause he was afraid he wouldn't be able to get them back on. When he had to move or sit up so I could wash him, he shut \expndtw-3 his eyes.\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\par
\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\li2347\sl-197\slmult0\qc\par
\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\li264\sl-197\slmult0\cf1\lang1033\expndtw-1\fs21 "Am I really here?" he asked. "Am I here?"\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\fs20\par
\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi245\li19\ri5\sl-197\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw1\fs21 "Yes," I said. "You are here. What I don't understand is \expndtw-2 how you got here."\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\fs20\par
\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi240\li19\ri10\sl-197\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw-2\fs21 "Oh, it wasn't bad so long as I kept moving. All you need \expndtw-5 is to know where you're going-to have someplace to go. You \expndtw-4 know, some of the people in Camp, if they'd let them go, they \expndtw-1 wouldn't have had that. They couldn't have gone anywhere. \expndtw-5 Keeping moving was the main thing. See, my back's all seized \expndtw-4 up, now."\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\fs20\par
\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi250\li5\ri10\sl-197\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\fs21 When he had to get up to go to the bathroom he moved \expndtw-2 like a ninety-year-old. He couldn't stand straight, but was all \expndtw-1 bent out of shape, and shuffled. I helped him put on clean \expndtw-2 clothes. When he lay down on the bed again, a sound of pain \expndtw-1 came out of him, like tearing thick paper. I went around the room putting things away. He asked me to come sit by him \expndtw-4 and said I was going to drown him if I went on crying. "You'll \expndtw1 submerge the entire North American continent," he said. I \expndtw-1 can't remember what he said, but he made me laugh finally. \expndtw1 It is hard to remember things Simon says, and hard not to laugh when he says them. This is not merely the partiality \expndtw-1 of affection: He makes everybody laugh. I doubt that he in\-\expndtw2 tends to. It is just that a mathematician's mind works dif\-\expndtw0 ferently from other people's. Then when they laugh, that \expndtw-1 pleases him.\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\fs20\par
\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi245\li5\sl-197\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw3\fs21 It was strange, and it is strange, to be thinking about \expndtw1 "him," the man I have known for ten years, the same man, \expndtw-1 while "he" lay there changed out of recognition, a different \expndtw0 man. It is enough to make you understand why most lan\-\expndtw-2 guages have a word like "soul." There are various degrees of death, and time spares us none of them. Yet something en\-\expndtw-1 dures, for which a word is needed.\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\fs20\par
