\pard\cbpat2\nowidctlpar\fi254\ri24\sl-197\slmult0\qj\cf1\lang1033\expndtw3 I went out again to register Simon as 'temporarily domi\-ciled at my address and to apply for Temporary Unemploy\-ment Compensation ration stamps for him. They, only give \expndtw1 them to you for two weeks and you have to come every day; \expndtw4 but to register him as Temporarily Disabled meant getting \expndtw3 the signatures of two fed-meds, and I thought I'd rather put \expndtw5 that off for a while. It took three hours to go through the lines and get the forms he would have to fill out, and to \expndtw6 answer the 'crats' questions about why he wasn't there in \expndtw1 person. They smelled something fishy. Of course it's hard for \expndtw4 them to prove that two people are married and aren't just adultering if you move now and then and your friends help\cf0\lang2057\expndtw0\par
